The paper deals with interference analysis in small cell networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a new framework for analyzing interference in complex networks, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) or multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of lognormal distributions, which could be relevant to game theory (cs.GT) or machine learning (cs.LG).
